You can say, “We changed the law and we allowed it,” but you can’t say we’ll do it like nothing.
In the Public Procurement Act, the regulation is quite strict as to how it should be formally acted, and that is how it should be to protect public competition.
But, on the other hand, it is tragic that the candidate with the best offer is excluded for not meeting the formal requirements.
The law will never be perfect, but its application must be correct, which, in my opinion, is what we are missing.
